TY  - JOUR
AU  - Ready, Mark J
AU  - Ready, Robert C
T1  - Order Flows and Financial Investor Impacts in Commodity Futures Markets
PY  - 2022
Y1  - 2022/10/01
DO  - 10.1093/rfs/hhac008
JO  - The Review of Financial Studies
JA  - Rev Financ Stud
VL  - 35
IS  - 10
SP  - 4712
EP  - 4755
SN  - 0893-9454
AB  - Using intraday data, we document statistically strong, but temporary, impacts of commodity index trade flows on commodity futures prices. We also examine the previously documented positive returns around the issuance of commodity-linked notes and find that these returns are an order of magnitude too large to be caused by the small trades necessary to hedge the notes. We provide new evidence that they are instead the result of endogenous issuance. Our results provide novel support for commodity financialization but highlight the importance of measuring the magnitude of financial investment, since even large financial flows have economically modest impacts on prices.
Y2  - 3/26/2024
UR  - https://doi.org/10.1093/rfs/hhac008
ER  - 



