TY  - JOUR
AU  - Celik, Murat Alp
AU  - Tian, Xu
AU  - Wang, Wenyu
T1  - Acquiring Innovation under Information Frictions*
PY  - 2022
Y1  - 2022/10/01
DO  - 10.1093/rfs/hhac006
JO  - The Review of Financial Studies
JA  - Rev Financ Stud
VL  - 35
IS  - 10
SP  - 4474
EP  - 4517
SN  - 0893-9454
AB  - Acquiring innovation through M&amp;A is subject to information frictions, as assessing the value of innovative targets is a challenging task. We find an inverted U-shaped relation between firm innovation and takeover exposure; equity usage increases with target innovation; and the deal completion rate drops with innovation. We develop and estimate a model of acquiring innovation under information frictions, featuring endogenous merger, innovation, and offer composition decisions. Our estimates suggest that acquirers’ due diligence reveals only 30$\%$ of private information possessed by targets. Eliminating information frictions increases capitalized merger gains by 59$\%$, stimulates innovation, and boosts productivity, business dynamism, and social welfare.
Y2  - 3/26/2024
UR  - https://doi.org/10.1093/rfs/hhac006
ER  - 



